stork.scheduler

Class Scheduler

  • java.lang.Object
    • stork.scheduler.Scheduler

  • public class Scheduler
extends Object
    The Stork transfer job scheduler. Maintains its own internal configuration and state as an ad. Operates based on commands given to it in the form of ads. Can be run standalone and receive commands from a number of interfaces, or can be run as part of a larger program and be given commands directly (or both). The entire state of the scheduler can be serialized and saved to disk, and subsequently recovered if so desired. TODO: This thing could use some refactoring.
